name: PrescribableBrandAndGenericInsulinsAndAnalogues
title: Prescribable brand and generic insulins and analogues
purpose: (Clinical Focus: The purpose of this value set is to represent concepts for both brand and generic prescribable insulins and insulin analogues used to manage hyperglycemia in Diabetes Mellitus),(Data Element Scope: Any medication data element which references prescribable, insulins and insulin analogues used to manage hyperglycemia in Diabetes Mellitus using SBD and SCD RxNorm TTYs),(Inclusion Criteria: Drugs containing an ingredient in the ATC1-4 class Insulins and Analogues, which are prescribable and have an RxNorm Term Type of Semantic Clinical Drug (SCD) or Semantic Branded Drug (SBD)),(Exclusion Criteria: Non-prescribable drugs or codes which are not of TTY SBD or SCD)
